# Gensyn AXL

AXL is a P2P network node. Your app talks to localhost:9002 via HTTP.

Key endpoints:
- POST /send — send message to a peer (by their public key)
- GET /recv — receive pending messages
- GET /topology — see connected peers
- /mcp/* — built-in MCP router for structured agent communication
- /a2a/* — built-in A2A server for agent-to-agent protocols

MUST demonstrate communication across SEPARATE AXL nodes (not in-process).

# KeeperHub

Execution layer for on-chain operations. Connect via MCP server or CLI.
- MCP: HTTP-based MCP server at https://mcp.keeperhub.com/sse
- CLI: `kh` command (install via homebrew: `brew install KeeperHub/tap/kh`)
- Supports x402 and MPP payment protocols
- Provides: retry logic, gas optimization, MEV protection, audit trails

# x402 Protocol

HTTP 402 payment flow:
1. Client requests paid resource
2. Server returns 402 with PAYMENT-REQUIRED header (amount, asset, payTo, chain)
3. Client signs payment on-chain (USDC on Base)
4. Client retries with X-PAYMENT header containing signed proof
5. Server verifies payment and returns resource

Bazaar discovery: GET /discovery/resources from facilitator URL

